WEBVTT

00:00:00.938 --> 00:00:06.735 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve got this grudge.
I’m holding it in.

00:00:06.735 --> 00:00:13.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But it’s so heavy;
it pulls me down.

00:00:13.367 --> 00:00:19.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wish I could
turn this around.

00:00:19.540 --> 00:00:26.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I understand
the need to forgive,

00:00:26.797 --> 00:00:32.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But it’s not easy
if it’s not my fault.

00:00:32.303 --> 00:00:38.976 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
These thoughts
bring forgiveness to a halt.

00:00:38.976 --> 00:00:44.356 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s right about now
that I have to pray.

00:00:44.356 --> 00:00:49.361 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah saw what happened;
he knows my pain.

00:00:49.361 --> 00:00:54.325 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But most of all
he gives me

00:00:54.325 --> 00:00:59.204 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Strength to let it go.

00:00:59.204 --> 00:01:04.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No, I can’t do this
on my own.

00:01:04.460 --> 00:01:14.345 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I pray, “Jehovah, please help me;
Help me forgive freely.”

00:01:14.345 --> 00:01:23.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’ll help me to reflect
The way he forgives, the way he forgets.

